Exercise 2.1 — Bootstrap Structure and Files

When Bootstrap is downloaded or installed, it contains different folders and files required for styling and interactive features.

A typical Bootstrap directory structure looks like this:

bootstrap/
│
├── css/
│     ├── bootstrap.css
│     ├── bootstrap.min.css
│     ├── bootstrap-grid.css
│     └── bootstrap-utilities.css
│
├── js/
│     ├── bootstrap.js
│     ├── bootstrap.bundle.js
│     └── bootstrap.bundle.min.js
│
└── icons/
      ├── fonts/
      └── bootstrap-icons.css
1. CSS Folder

The css folder contains Bootstrap styling files.

Purpose

It is used to:

Design webpages
Apply layouts
Add colors, spacing, buttons, forms, tables, etc.
Important CSS Files
File Name	Purpose
bootstrap.css	Full Bootstrap CSS file
bootstrap.min.css	Compressed version for faster loading
bootstrap-grid.css	Contains only grid system
bootstrap-utilities.css	Contains utility classes
Example
<link rel="stylesheet"
      href="node_modules/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">

This file gives Bootstrap styles to the webpage.

2. JS Folder

The js folder contains JavaScript files.

Purpose

Used for interactive Bootstrap components such as:

Modal
Carousel
Dropdown
Tooltip
Collapse
Navbar toggle

Without JS files, these components will not work properly.

Important JS Files
File Name	Purpose
bootstrap.js	Main Bootstrap JavaScript
bootstrap.bundle.js	Includes Bootstrap + Popper.js
bootstrap.bundle.min.js	Minified version for production
Example
<script src="node_modules/bootstrap/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>

This enables Bootstrap interactive features.

3. Icons Folder

The icons folder contains Bootstrap Icons.

Purpose

Used to add icons such as:

Home
Search
User
Bell
Menu
Cart

These icons improve webpage appearance and user experience.

Important Files
File Name	Purpose
bootstrap-icons.css	Icon styling file
fonts/	Stores icon font files
Example
<link rel="stylesheet"
href="icons/bootstrap-icons.css">

Using an icon:

<i class="bi bi-house-fill"></i>